Write a method named 'generateSequence' that takes an integer as input. The method should generate a sequence of consecutive numbers from 1 up to the given upper bound integer, inclusive.

For every number in the sequence, if it's evenly divisible by 4, increase it tenfold by multiplying it by 10; otherwise, leave the number unchanged. The method should return a list containing the generated sequence of numbers.
For example for given integer 10, the method should return {1, 2, 3, 40, 5, 6, 7, 80, 9, 10}

solution:
 public List<Integer> generateSequence(Integer num) {
    if (num == null || num <= 0) {
        return new List<Integer>();
    }

    List<Integer> sequence = new List<Integer>();
    for (Integer i = 1; i <= num; i++) {
        if (Math.mod(i, 4) == 0) {
            sequence.add(i * 10);
        } else {
            sequence.add(i);
        }
    }
    return sequence;
}

