Create a class named PaymentService with a method named getPaymentLink. This method should make a GET request to the payment endpoint, parse the JSON response, and return the payment link from the payer object.

Endpoint: https://735ef563-176d-431c-85ce-2cc07056ef03.mock.pstmn.io/payments/link

The JSON structure is: { "payer": { "link": "https://..." } }

Use JSON.deserializeUntyped to convert the response body to a Map<String, Object>, then get the payer object (also a Map), and finally get the link.

Method signature:
public String getPaymentLink()

solution:
public class PaymentService {
    public String getPaymentLink() {
        HttpRequest request = new HttpRequest();
        request.setEndpoint('https://735ef563-176d-431c-85ce-2cc07056ef03.mock.pstmn.io/payments/link');
        request.setMethod('GET');
        Http http = new Http();
        HttpResponse response = http.send(request);
        String responseBody = response.getBody();
        Map<String, Object> responseAsMap = (Map<String, Object>) JSON.deserializeUntyped(responseBody);
        Map<String, Object> payer = (Map<String, Object>) responseAsMap.get('payer');
        String paymentLink = (String) payer.get('link');
        return paymentLink;
    }
}

