description:
Create a class named InvoiceProcessor in your org with three methods:

1. getInvoiceId - returns the 'invoiceId' field as String
2. getTotal - returns the 'total' field as Decimal
3. getLineItemCount - returns the number of items in the 'lineItems' array as Integer

Example JSON: {"invoiceId": "INV-2024-001", "total": 1250.00, "paid": false, "lineItems": ["Service A", "Service B", "Service C"], "notes": null}

Method signatures:
public String getInvoiceId(String jsonString)
public Decimal getTotal(String jsonString)
public Integer getLineItemCount(String jsonString)

solution:
public class InvoiceProcessor {
    public String getInvoiceId(String jsonString) {
        Map<String, Object> data = (Map<String, Object>) JSON.deserializeUntyped(jsonString);
        return (String) data.get('invoiceId');
    }

    public Decimal getTotal(String jsonString) {
        Map<String, Object> data = (Map<String, Object>) JSON.deserializeUntyped(jsonString);
        return (Decimal) data.get('total');
    }

    public Integer getLineItemCount(String jsonString) {
        Map<String, Object> data = (Map<String, Object>) JSON.deserializeUntyped(jsonString);
        List<Object> lineItems = (List<Object>) data.get('lineItems');
        return lineItems.size();
    }
}

